            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#bramsonJ" start="3952.099" end="x">Perished . . . and so resistance began to be organized seriously at the end of '42. The period of initial organization was over. And then started the open fight. This open fight was led by many methods. First of all the terror activities. It was accepted that the Germans should not be in peace, that they should feel in France as if on a volcano, and for this reason either their automobiles were attacked, or mines were placed under trains, or the quarters of the <a class="term" href="#vothG_gestapo">Gestapo</a>, were bombed, or the staff offices, etc.</span>
