                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">Jacques Bramson</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#bramsonJ" start="x" end="x">But I had . . . I wanted it that way, because I was wounded . . . I had on me official military documents. I did not want to be taken for a partisan. Since I considered myself anyway a doomed man, since I had wounded the Chief of the <a class="term" href="#vothG_gestapo">Gestapo</a>, at the moment of arrest, I said to myself, let them better shoot me as a military, than hang me like a dog. [<i>he laughs</i>] . . . At the first grilling I managed to avoid an important fact. I was grilled by an officer of the German counter-intelligence.</span>
        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">David Boder</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#boderD" start="x" end="x">So.</span>
