            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#bramsonJ" start="x" end="x">And so I was registered and since then I was not questioned about race up to my transfer to <placeName type="camp" ref="#vothC22">Compiègne</a>.<note n="42"><span class="note">The Nazi racist ideology incorrectly viewed the Jews as a "race" when in fact they are members of a religion and a people. Mr. Bramson uses this racist terminology common at the time. The camp at Compiègne, located in north central France, was founded in December, 1941. As he later relates, it was from Compiègne that Mr. Bramson was deported to Buchenwald.</span><sup><a href="#note_42">42</a></sup></note> In <a class="placename" href="#vothL20">Périgueux</a> I spent ten days. During these ten days there was an attempt to deliver us [from captivity] and the <a class="term" href="#vothG_gestapo">Gestapo</a> in <a class="placename" href="#vothL20">Périgueux</a> went up in the air.</span>
