            <span class="utterance" who="#bramsonJ" start="4859.835" end="x">It was like this. Before surrendering the <a class="term" href="#vothG_lager">lager</a>
                        <a class="placename" href="#vothC15" type="camp">Buchenwald</a> to the Americans, the Germans selected fifteen thousand people, whom they said they had decided to send away as hostages.<note n="54"><span class="note">Before the arrival of American forces, the SS evacuated prisoners of various nationalities from the main camp and the satellite camps on what became death marches.</span><sup><a href="#note_54">54</a></sup></note></span>
        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">David Boder</span>:
