                <strong>Location:</strong>
                Compi&#195;gne, France<br />
                            </p>
                            <div>
                This detention camp operated from June 1941 to August 1944 and was located in the French commune of Compi&#195;gne. Prisoners included French Communists, Resistance fighters, and Soviet citizens as well as Jews.
            </div>
